wrlinux-cgl
======

This layer provides the Carrier Grade components for Wind River Linux.


Dependencies
------------
This layer depends on the following layers:
  meta-cgl-common
  meta-networking
  meta-oe
  meta-perl
  meta-python
  meta-security
  meta-selinux
  meta-webserver
  openembedded-core
  wrlinux
  wrlinux-distro
  wr-template
  wr-template

The layer also recommends the following layers:
  wrlinux-cgl-dl

Maintenance
-----------
This layer is maintained by Wind River Systems, Inc.
Contact <support@windriver.com> or your support representative for more
information on submitting changes.


Building the wrlinux-cgl layer
-------------------------
This layer should be added to the bblayers.conf file, as well as any required layers.

To enable the 'wrlinux-cgl' distribution, you will need to setup with:

--distro wrlinux-cgl

or set the following in local.conf file:

DISTRO = "wrlinux-cgl"


